Module com.jlbabilino.json
Package com.jlbabilino.json

Class JSONNull

java.lang.Object
com.jlbabilino.json.JSONEntry
com.jlbabilino.json.JSONNull
public class JSONNull extends JSONEntry

This class wraps a null value in a JSONEntry. A JSON null is essentially the same as a Java null, it possesses no information, and no null is any different than another. For this reason, there is only ever one instance of this class, and it can be accessed through the field JSONNull.NULL.

Because of this property, all JSONNull values can be correctly compared using the == operator. To check if a JSONEntry is null, you can either use isNull() or == JSONNull.NULL.
